See https://github.com/alebsack/rack-fiber_pool/blob/master/example/app.rb
rack-fiber_pool
  https://github.com/alebsack/rack-fiber_pool
  https://github.com/mperham/rack-fiber_pool/
  A Rack middleware component which runs each request in a Fiber from a pool of Fibers.
  You need a EventMachine-based server (e.g. thin or rainbows)

Based on FiberPool https://github.com/JonRowe/FiberPool
  An implementation of a fiber pool that can be used to cooperatively schedule workloads.
  Best used in combination with EventMachine to allow multiple workloads to be processed at the same time.

http://rubylearning.com/blog/a-quick-introduction-to-rack/
by Satish Salim
